                "caption": "Figure 1:LingBot-Visionlearns dense representations via boundary-centric masked modeling.Each row, from left to right: the input image; the PCA projection of the frozen teacher’s patch tokens; boundary tokens (pink) obtained by a-contrario validation of dense line proposals decoded from the model’s own boundary-field prediction, overlaid on the accumulated response of the validated proposals; and cosine-similarity maps between nine boundary-token queries (red crosses, selected by farthest-point sampling in feature space) and all patch tokens.\nThe learned representations carry both semantic grouping and geometric structures.\nInput images are at 1024px for the short side.",
